  "Frame Cramps and Channel Ties": {
    "description": "Frame cramps with a single 7mm diameter hole or an 8mm x 30mm vertical slot can be fixed to concrete, steelwork or masonry. M6 Single Expansion bolts are recommended for fixing to concrete, setscrews or self-drilling screws for steelwork, and suitable plugs and screws for fixing to masonry. Poor substrates will limit the capacity of frame cramps and site treating is advisable in some cases. The performance will also be determined by the position of the fixing. Channel ties fixed to steelwork or concrete at the lowest point of slot will have a safe working load of approximately 1kN. The capacity will reduce as the fixing is moved further away from the bend and greater movement shall be expected than with other wall ties.",
